  "sections": {
    "Description": "Raging Psions are identifiable by their squid-like black body and beige bumps. While alive, they grant all other Vek the boosted effect, increasing their damage by 1.\nPsions can only spawn once per mission. ThePsionic Receiverboosts all mechs when a Raging Psion is present.",
    "Strategy": "Since Boost increases damage by 1, this means even regular non-alpha enemies are capable of downing tiles with 2 buildings at once, making the Raging Psion particularly dangerous to the power grid in the early-game.\nHowever, if using Mechs that can easily redirect Vek attacks into other enemies, it is preferable to let the Raging Psion live as long as possible in order to turn enemies against each other for higher damage. The Psionic Receiver passive is also particularly effective against the Raging Psion, letting the players Mechs take advantage of its passive Boost every turn that it is present."
  },
  "full_text": "Raging Psion\nDetails\nHealth\n2\nMove\n2\nSystems\nRaging Hormones\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nAll other Vek are\nBoosted\n, providing +1 damage to attacks.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nThe\nRaging Psion\nis one of the\nVek\npsions from\nInto The Breach\nintroduced in the Advanced Edition. They are only present if Advanced Enemies are turned on at the start of a new timeline.\nDescription\n[\n]\nRaging Psions are identifiable by their squid-like black body and beige bumps. While alive, they grant all other Vek the boosted effect, increasing their damage by 1.\nPsions can only spawn once per mission. The\nPsionic Receiver\nboosts all mechs when a Raging Psion is present.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nSince Boost increases damage by 1, this means even regular non-alpha enemies are capable of downing tiles with 2 buildings at once, making the Raging Psion particularly dangerous to the power grid in the early-game.\nHowever, if using Mechs that can easily redirect Vek attacks into other enemies, it is preferable to let the Raging Psion live as long as possible in order to turn enemies against each other for higher damage. The Psionic Receiver passive is also particularly effective against the Raging Psion, letting the players Mechs take advantage of its passive Boost every turn that it is present.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
}